        "timestamp": "2018-04-26 19:33:07.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nLiam Code Review Comments:\n=========================\n(6 comments)\n\nI checked the two classes this morning. I think they are fine except for the minor issue with closing the old connection when the URL changes.\nPolicyEngineAPI/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/std/AutoClientEnd.java\nLine 27:\n\nWe don't need this import for the new WS library\nLine 38:\n\nWe don't need this annotation for the new WS library\nLine 139:\n\nOK, start does nothing if the client is already started :-)\nLine 184:\n\nI think we need to do a stop() before changing to the new URL, otherwise when we call start() we'll overwrite the URL on line  136 and then we'll come to the if statement on line 138/139 and see that \"AutoClientEnd.client != null\" and finish. We'll have the situation with the client configured with the new URL but still happily connected to the web socket at the old URL.\nPolicyEngineAPI/src/main/java/org/onap/policy/std/ManualClientEnd.java\nLine 25:\n\nWe don't need this import for the new WS library\nLine 36:\n\nWe don't need this annotation for the new WS library",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
